\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 23. N. bicolor} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} ed. 2, 415 (1762). Bulb 25-35 mm. Leaves 30-35 cm × 10-14 mm. Scape 30-40 cm. Spathe 25-40 mm, scarious. Flowers solitary, horizontal. Pedicel 15-35 mm. Hypanthial tube 8-12 mm. Perianth-segments 35-40 mm, cream-coloured to pale yellow, erecto-patent, not twisted. Corona 35-40 mm, deep yellow; margin scarcely expanded, entire or slightly crenulate.{\i  Mountain meadows. • Pyrenees and Corbières.} Ga Hs.
\par

