\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 24. N. minor} L.,{\i  Sp. Pl.} ed. 2, 415 (1762). Bulb 20-30 mm. Leaves 8-20(-25) cm × 3-10 mm, glaucous. Scape 8-25 cm. Spathe 25-40 mm, scarious. Flowers solitary, horizontal or drooping. Pedicel 3-20 mm. Hypanthial tube 9-15 mm. Perianth-segments 16-22 mm, very pale to deep yellow, erectopatent, sometimes twisted. Corona 16-25 mm, deep yellow margin variously lobed or dentate. 2n = 14. {\i Mountain grassland and open scrub. • Pyrenees and N. Spain; naturalized in S.E. France.} Ga Hs.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28  The circumscription and distribution of this species are subject to some doubt. Records from N. Portugal and N.W. Spain appear to be referable to {\b 25}, or perhaps in some cases to hybrids between {\b 22} and {\b 25}.
\par

