\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 25. N. asturiensis} (Jordan) Pugsley, {\i Jour. Roy. Hort. Soc. }{\b 58}: 40 (1933). Bulb 15-20 mm. Leaves 5-15 cm × 2-6 mm, glaucous. Scape 7-10(-20) cm. Spathe 15-22(-28) mm, greenish at anthesis, scarious later. Flowers solitary, usually drooping, concolorous, medium yellow. Pedicel 3-10 mm. Hypanthial tube 5-9 mm. Perianth-segments 7-14 mm, erecto-patent, not twisted. Corona 8-16 mm, constricted in the middle and expanded towards the apex; margin somewhat lobed or laciniate. 2n = 14, 15. •{\i  N. Portugal, N.W. & N.C. Spain.} Hs Lu.
